**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:

According to the [docs](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/indices-get-index.html#get-index-api-query-params)
> ignore_unavailable (Optional, boolean) If true, missing or closed indices are not included in the response. Defaults to false.

I would expect `ignore_unavailable=true` not to include a closed index in the response. However this query parameter has no effect on the response for a closed index:
```
$ curl -X PUT "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/closed"
{"acknowledged":true,"shards_acknowledged":true,"index":"closed"}
$ curl -X POST "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/closed/_close"
{"acknowledged":true,"shards_acknowledged":true,"indices":{"closed":{"closed":true}}}
$ curl -X GET "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/closed?ignore_unavailable=true"
{"closed":{"aliases":{},"mappings":{},"settings":{"index":{"routing":{"allocation":{"include":{"_tier_preference":"data_content"}}},"verified_before_close":"true","number_of_shards":"1","provided_name":"closed","creation_date":"1602592899705","number_of_replicas":"1","uuid":"P2g6SySbTCCrroQ_EvkQTw","version":{"created":"8000099"}}}}}
$ curl -X GET "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/closed?ignore_unavailable=false"
{"closed":{"aliases":{},"mappings":{},"settings":{"index":{"routing":{"allocation":{"include":{"_tier_preference":"data_content"}}},"verified_before_close":"true","number_of_shards":"1","provided_name":"closed","creation_date":"1602592899705","number_of_replicas":"1","uuid":"P2g6SySbTCCrroQ_EvkQTw","version":{"created":"8000099"}}}}}
```

This query parameter does change the behaviour for missing indices. When querying a missing index it will not return an error when `ignore_unavailable=true`
```
$ curl -X GET "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/closed,missing?ignore_unavailable=false"
{"error":{"root_cause":[{"type":"index_not_found_exception","reason":"no such index [missing]","resource.type":"index_or_alias","resource.id":"missing","index_uuid":"_na_","index":"missing"}],"type":"index_not_found_exception","reason":"no such index [missing]","resource.type":"index_or_alias","resource.id":"missing","index_uuid":"_na_","index":"missing"},"status":404}
$ curl -X GET "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/closed,missing?ignore_unavailable=true"
{"closed":{"aliases":{},"mappings":{},"settings":{"index":{"routing":{"allocation":{"include":{"_tier_preference":"data_content"}}},"verified_before_close":"true","number_of_shards":"1","provided_name":"closed","creation_date":"1602592899705","number_of_replicas":"1","uuid":"P2g6SySbTCCrroQ_EvkQTw","version":{"created":"8000099"}}}}}
```

For the Get Index Alias API, `ignore_unavailable` doesn't seem to change any behaviour for missing or closed indices [documentation](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/indices-get-alias.html). 
```
$ curl -X PUT "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/closed"
{"acknowledged":true,"shards_acknowledged":true,"index":"closed"}
$ curl -X POST "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/closed/_close"
{"acknowledged":true,"shards_acknowledged":true,"indices":{"closed":{"closed":true}}}
$ curl -X PUT "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/closed/_alias/closed_alias"
{"acknowledged":true}
$ curl -X GET "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/_alias/closed_alias,missing?ignore_unavailable=false"
{"error":"alias [missing] missing","status":404,"closed":{"aliases":{"closed_alias":{}}}}
$ curl -X GET "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/_alias/closed_alias,missing?ignore_unavailable=true"
{"error":"alias [missing] missing","status":404,"closed":{"aliases":{"closed_alias":{}}}}
$ curl -X GET "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/_alias/closed_alias?ignore_unavailable=true"
{"closed":{"aliases":{"closed_alias":{}}}}
$ curl -X GET "elastic:changeme@localhost:9200/_alias/closed_alias?ignore_unavailable=false"
{"closed":{"aliases":{"closed_alias":{}}}}
```

If you write a date range query with numeric parameters we *can* interpret them as a year. Check it out:

```
curl -XDELETE -uelastic:password localhost:9200/test
curl -XPOST -HContent-Type:application/json -uelastic:password localhost:9200/test/_doc?refresh -d'{"d": "1970-01-01T00:00:01.010Z"}'
curl -XPOST -HContent-Type:application/json -uelastic:password localhost:9200/test/_doc?refresh -d'{"d": "1967-01-01T00:00:00.000Z"}'
curl -XPOST -HContent-Type:application/json -uelastic:password localhost:9200/test/_search?pretty -d'{
  "query": {
    "range": {
      "d": {
        "gt": 1000
      }
    }
  }
}'
```

The `1000` gets turned into a String internally and then we parse it as the year 1000.

